#: ../../../index.rst:135
msgid ""
"Read the Docs simplifies managing software documentation by building and "
"hosting your docs automatically, using the Git workflow you already use for "
"code. Treating documentation like code lets your team use tools they already "
"know, and makes keeping your docs updated easier."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../index.rst:141
msgid "Up to date documentation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../index.rst:142
msgid ""
"Whenever you push code to Git, Read the Docs will automatically build your "
"docs so your code and documentation are always up-to-date. Get started with "
"our :doc:`tutorial </tutorial/index>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../index.rst:147
msgid "Documentation for every version"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../index.rst:148
msgid ""
"Read the Docs can host multiple versions of your docs. Keep your 1.0 and 2.0 "
"documentation online, pulled directly from Git. Start hosting all your :doc:"
"`versions </versions>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../index.rst:153
msgid "Open source and user focused"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../index.rst:154
msgid ""
"Our company is bootstrapped and 100% user-focused, so our product gets "
"better for our users instead of our investors. |org_brand| hosts "
"documentation for over 100,000 large and small open source projects at no "
"cost. |com_brand| supports hundreds of organizations with product and "
"internal documentation. Learn more about these differences on `our pricing "
"page <https://about.readthedocs.com/pricing/>`_."
